<question>
  <p>
  <ol>
    <li> Is the point <m>(1,2,3)</m> on the cone <m>z^2=x^2+y^2</m>? Be sure to explain your answer.</li>
    <li> Show that the vector valued function
      <me>\overrightarrow{\textbf{r}}(t)=\langle e^{-t}\cos(t) , e^{-t}\sin(t),e^{-t} \rangle</me>
      lies on the cone <m>z^2=x^2+y^2</m>.</li>
  </ol>
  </p>
</question>
<question>
  <p>
